latestPosts.caption:
Blood clotting factors, also known as coagulation factors, are a group of plasma proteins that play a crucial role in hemostasis, the process by which the body stops bleeding. When a blood vessel is injured, a complex cascade of reactions involving these clotting factors leads to the formation of a blood clot, preventing excessive blood loss.

List of Blood Clotting Factors:
| Factor Number | Name |

| I | Fibrinogen |
| II | Prothrombin |
| III | Tissue Factor (Tissue Thromboplastin) |
| IV | Calcium ions |
| V | Labile Factor (Proaccelerin) |
| VII | Stable Factor (Proconvertin) |
| VIII | Antihemophilic Factor A |
| IX | Christmas Factor (Plasma Thromboplastin Component) |
| X | Stuart-Prower Factor |
| XI | Plasma Thromboplastin Antecedent |
| XII | Hageman Factor |
| XIII | Fibrin-Stabilizing Factor |
